<h2>PNG vs JPG: Which Format Should You Choose?</h2>

<p>Choose PNG when you need:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Pixel-perfect lossless quality (no compression artefacts)</li>
  <li>Transparency support (useful for diagrams with non-white backgrounds)</li>
  <li>Screenshots, diagrams, charts, or text-heavy content</li>
  <li>Images that will be further edited or re-saved multiple times</li>
</ul>

<p>Choose JPG when you need:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Smaller file sizes (JPG photos are typically 50–80% smaller than equivalent PNG)</li>
  <li>Photographs or photo-heavy content where minor quality loss is acceptable</li>
  <li>Images for the web where loading speed matters more than perfect quality</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Convert PDF to PNG on Windows</h2>

<p>Besides the browser tool above, Windows options include:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Open the PDF in Edge, right-click a page → "Save as image" (Edge now supports saving PDF pages as PNG).</li>
  <li><strong>Paint or Snipping Tool:</strong> Open the PDF in any viewer, use the Snipping Tool to screenshot individual pages, and save as PNG.</li>
  <li><strong>Adobe Acrobat (paid):</strong> File → Export To → Image → PNG — gives full control over resolution and quality.</li>
  <li><strong>GIMP (free):</strong> Open the PDF in GIMP (it will ask for DPI), then export the layers as PNG files.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Convert PDF to PNG on Mac</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Preview (built-in):</strong> Open the PDF → File → Export → choose PNG as the format → save. Preview can export each page but requires doing them one at a time.</li>
  <li><strong>Automator:</strong> Mac's Automator app can batch-convert a multi-page PDF to PNG — search "PDF to Image" in Automator actions.</li>
  <li><strong>Browser tool:</strong> The PDFWonder converter above works on Mac the same as any other platform.</li>
</ul>

<h2>How to Convert PDF to PNG on iPhone and Android</h2>

<p>On mobile:</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open <a href="/pdfwonder/pdf-to-png">PDFWonder PDF to PNG</a> in your mobile browser (Safari or Chrome).</li>
  <li>Tap the upload area and select your PDF from Files or Google Drive.</li>
  <li>Tap the download button for each page to save PNGs directly to your camera roll or downloads folder.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Use Cases for PDF to PNG Conversion</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Presentations:</strong> Embed specific PDF pages as high-quality images in PowerPoint or Google Slides</li>
  <li><strong>Websites:</strong> Display PDF document previews as web images</li>
  <li><strong>Social media:</strong> Share individual report pages or infographics as PNG images</li>
  <li><strong>Email:</strong> Attach specific pages as inline images instead of sending the whole PDF</li>
  <li><strong>Editing:</strong> Import PDF content into image editing software like Photoshop or Canva</li>
</ul>

